	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Thursday&#44; Pericope</date>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)">M&#39;tzorang &#40;<date>March</date>&#41;</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>1864</date>.</p>
				<p>To the excellent <addressee>Rabbi Eliezar Lippman</addressee><lb/> <addressee>Leeser</addressee> of the Sephardic Congregation&#58; I<lb/> received your kind letter today&#44; and I<lb/> reply that I can send you a Sefer Torah&#44;<lb/> about 28 inches in size&#44; not new.  It<lb/> will amount to at least &#36;90.  This<lb/> I shall do for the sake of my dear trusting<lb/> friends so that the Goyim might not<lb/> say&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;.  And as to why I have<lb/> not yet sent the T&#39;phillin&#44; please believe<lb/> me that I have not received the things<lb/> from the workmen for they are overloaded<lb/> with work and this is a secondary matter<lb/> with them.  With regard to the Sefer Torah&#44;<lb/> reply to me at once and I shall take some<lb/> time to look through it and<lb/> correct what mistakes I find&#59; so as to<lb/> send it to you &#8220;Kosher&#8221; Then I shall<lb/> order a new &#8220;Etz Chaim&#8221; &#40;The wooden rollers&#41;&#44;<lb/> so that it might reach you in<lb/> proper shape.  At the same time I&#39;ll send<lb/> some T&#39;phillim&#44; mezuzot&#44; and Tsizit.<lb/>  <del>If you will</del> Reply to me at once&#44; so that</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>you will receive the Sefer Torah before<lb/> <date>Passover</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I hope to receive your answer.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your friend <sic>an</sic> Servant&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Elijah</persName>&#44; son of <persName>Moses</persName>&#44; Scribe.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">E. M. Holzman</persName>.</p>
				<p>I request an immediate answer&#44; in<lb/> order that I may justify myself&#59; if<lb/> not <del>you will receive the Sefer Torah only</del> then we will be able to see each other<lb/> only after <date>Passover</date>&#44; when&#44; God willing&#44;<lb/> I shall be in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.  At that time<lb/> I hope&#44; I shall be able to make my<lb/> enemies&#44; &#8220;look like the rim of a pot&#44;&#8221;<lb/> and God will grant you goodness and<lb/> life and that you will celebrate the<lb/> <date>passover</date> in joy.</p>
		</body>
